## Germplasm Phenotype:
   - [HUA2-Sy-0 ag-4]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;In the double mutant plants, fertile stamens were replaced by sterile petaloid stamens.
   - [Sy-0]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;Late-flowering A. thaliana accession characterized by an enlarged basal rosette, formation of aerial rosettes in the axils of stem leaves, and reversion of early floral meristems to indeterminate growth, a phenomenon known as floral reversion.
   - [hua2-1]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;Enhanced floral defects in weak agamous mutant allele ag-4
   - [hua2-2]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;Early flowering.
   - [hua2-4]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;Early flowering in long and short days.
   - [hua2-5]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;Early flowering in long and short days.
   - [hua2-6]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;Early flowering in short days.
